">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Good but More Scope of Improvement</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/srinivas08\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ee226585d77b89eedaa470b8ae210db?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ee226585d77b89eedaa470b8ae210db?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/srinivas08\" class=\"reviewer-name\">srinivas08</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">October 4, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The form is too simple, it cant be added directly, mostly it needs some css to make it work. If we use WPForms, it has good frontend design, CF7 is just like a skeleton of form. And on most sites it throws 409 conflict error as the response code.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Pretty easy to use and it&#039;s free!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/westerngeomancy\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a70f64fe24b26e55f5d6846231053f7a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a70f64fe24b26e55f5d6846231053f7a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/westerngeomancy\" class=\"reviewer-name\">westerngeomancy</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">October 2, 2021</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I was having trouble with Jetpack messing up anything more complicated than a basic contact form and looked at a few other plugins, all of which required subscription. I had thought CF7 seemed a bit complicated, but once I eventually took the plunge and installed it. Once you get your head around the tags formatting, it\'s really very easy to use, and very versatile; which encouraged me to set up even more complicated forms than I\'d previously used. \nAn excellent and essential plugin, huge thanks to the developer.\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">VERY SIMPLE!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>			